Subject: [PATCH 0/3] clk: sunxi-ng: a733: keep required fabric clocks enabled

This RFC series records the A733 CCU-side changes that allowed Radxa
Cubie A7S boot testing to move past two clock and fabric failures seen
with the A733 CCU, RTC, and pinctrl RFC dependencies.

Patch 1 keeps the CPUS AHB bridge enabled so later R-domain register
accesses remain live after clk_disable_unused(). Patch 2 keeps the
storage and NSI fabric bundle enabled; this is the conservative
hardware-verified shape, including mbus-msi-lite0 after a narrower
comparison without that gate failed before SDMMC0 initialization. Patch
3 commits the boot-programmed NSI clock state once during CCU probe using
the existing sunxi-ng update-bit mechanism.

The storage/NSI fabric and update-bit changes are split so maintainers
can decide whether this should remain local A733 CCU handling or move
toward a more explicit consumer/fabric model.


Enzo Adriano (3):
  clk: sunxi-ng: a733: keep the CPUS AHB bridge clock critical
  clk: sunxi-ng: a733: keep storage and NSI fabric clocks critical
  clk: sunxi-ng: a733: commit the boot-programmed NSI clock state

